<subSubSection lastPageId="2" pageId="1" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1750,2027]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,824]" lastPageId="2" pageId="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1750,1775]" pageId="1">Description.</emphasis>
Head with eyes distinctly narrower than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[881,946,1750,1775]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,760,783]" captionTargetBox="[265,1332,353,720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[241,1346,337,739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 1. holotype, dorsal view; 2. holotype, lateral view; 3. holotype, frontal view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216539/files/figure.png" pageId="1">
Fig. 
<number box="[933,946,1751,1775]" pageId="1" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metope and genae not extended to form a proboscis (
<figureCitation box="[274,344,1786,1811]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,760,783]" captionTargetBox="[265,1332,353,720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[241,1346,337,739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 1. holotype, dorsal view; 2. holotype, lateral view; 3. holotype, frontal view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216539/files/figure.png" pageId="1">
Fig. 
<number box="[327,344,1787,1811]" pageId="1" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Coryphe more or less quadrilateral, rough with fine granules, disc depressed; length in midline almost equal to width at two posterior angles (
<figureCitation box="[705,775,1822,1847]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,760,783]" captionTargetBox="[265,1332,353,720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[241,1346,337,739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 1. holotype, dorsal view; 2. holotype, lateral view; 3. holotype, frontal view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216539/files/figure.png" pageId="1">
Fig. 
<number box="[762,775,1823,1847]" pageId="1" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ocelli present. Metope with disc finely granulose and distinctly elevated, median carina present (
<figureCitation box="[638,708,1858,1883]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,760,783]" captionTargetBox="[265,1332,353,720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[241,1346,337,739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 1. holotype, dorsal view; 2. holotype, lateral view; 3. holotype, frontal view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216539/files/figure.png" pageId="1">
Fig. 
<number box="[692,708,1859,1883]" pageId="1" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metopoclypeal suture slightly arched. Postclypeus smooth, on same plane as metope, apical part curved downward (
<figureCitation box="[764,834,1894,1919]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="3.[151,264,760,783]" captionTargetBox="[265,1332,353,720]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[241,1346,337,739]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 1. holotype, dorsal view; 2. holotype, lateral view; 3. holotype, frontal view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216539/files/figure.png" pageId="1">
Fig. 
<number box="[818,834,1895,1919]" pageId="1" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Rostrum relatively long, exceeding mid-trochanter. Pronotum with anterior margin distinctly convex and posterior margin nearly truncate; disc finely granulose with median carina and two pits. Mesonotum nearly triangular, with pit on lateral margin; disc slightly elevated with fine granules, median carina present. Forewings coleopterous, nearly rectangular and rounded apically, costal margin nearly parallel to inner margin; claval suture absent, longitudinal veins present and distinct, irregular cross veins distinct (
<figureCitation box="[316,395,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[335,1226,885,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[320,1266,863,1870]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 22. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 4. forewing; 5. hind wing; 6. fore leg; 7. middle leg; 8. hind leg; 9. apex of hind leg; 10. male genitalia, lateral view; 11. anal tube, dorsal view; 12. penis, lateral view; 13. penis, dorsal view; 14. penis, ventral view; 15. capitulum of style, dorsal view; 16. female genitalia, ventral view; 17. anal tube, dorsal view; 18. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophyse VIII, lateral view; 19. gonapophyses IX, lateral view; 20. gonapophyses IX, dorsal view; 21. gonoplac, lateral view; 22. gonoplac, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216540/files/figure.png" pageId="2">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[407,439,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 27" captionStartId="4.[151,264,725,748]" captionTargetBox="[446,1149,205,690]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[415,1171,193,704]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 27. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 23. forewing; 24. male genitalia, lateral view; 25. penis and connective, lateral view; 26. apex of penis, dorsal view; 27. penis, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216541/files/figure.png" pageId="2">23</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[459,515,188,213]" name="India" pageId="2">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings reduced with vannus and anal lobe rudimentary, shorter than half length of forewings; veins indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[464,533,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[335,1226,885,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[320,1266,863,1870]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 22. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 4. forewing; 5. hind wing; 6. fore leg; 7. middle leg; 8. hind leg; 9. apex of hind leg; 10. male genitalia, lateral view; 11. anal tube, dorsal view; 12. penis, lateral view; 13. penis, dorsal view; 14. penis, ventral view; 15. capitulum of style, dorsal view; 16. female genitalia, ventral view; 17. anal tube, dorsal view; 18. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophyse VIII, lateral view; 19. gonapophyses IX, lateral view; 20. gonapophyses IX, dorsal view; 21. gonoplac, lateral view; 22. gonoplac, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216540/files/figure.png" pageId="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[517,533,223,248]" pageId="2" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs relatively long, fore and middle femora slightly foliate (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1345,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[335,1226,885,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[320,1266,863,1870]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 22. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 4. forewing; 5. hind wing; 6. fore leg; 7. middle leg; 8. hind leg; 9. apex of hind leg; 10. male genitalia, lateral view; 11. anal tube, dorsal view; 12. penis, lateral view; 13. penis, dorsal view; 14. penis, ventral view; 15. capitulum of style, dorsal view; 16. female genitalia, ventral view; 17. anal tube, dorsal view; 18. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophyse VIII, lateral view; 19. gonapophyses IX, lateral view; 20. gonapophyses IX, dorsal view; 21. gonoplac, lateral view; 22. gonoplac, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216540/files/figure.png" pageId="2">
Figs 
<number box="[1300,1345,223,248]" pageId="2" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
</figureCitation>
); lateral margin of hind tibia with 
<number box="[437,451,260,284]" pageId="2" value="3.0">3</number>
teeth (
<figureCitation box="[528,595,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[335,1226,885,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[320,1266,863,1870]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 22. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 4. forewing; 5. hind wing; 6. fore leg; 7. middle leg; 8. hind leg; 9. apex of hind leg; 10. male genitalia, lateral view; 11. anal tube, dorsal view; 12. penis, lateral view; 13. penis, dorsal view; 14. penis, ventral view; 15. capitulum of style, dorsal view; 16. female genitalia, ventral view; 17. anal tube, dorsal view; 18. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophyse VIII, lateral view; 19. gonapophyses IX, lateral view; 20. gonapophyses IX, dorsal view; 21. gonoplac, lateral view; 22. gonoplac, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216540/files/figure.png" pageId="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[580,595,260,284]" pageId="2" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Spinal formula of hind leg 
<number box="[920,932,260,284]" pageId="2" value="8.0">8</number>
– 
<number box="[948,960,260,284]" pageId="2" value="8.0">8</number>
– 
<number box="[976,990,260,284]" pageId="2" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[1005,1074,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[335,1226,885,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[320,1266,863,1870]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 22. Folifemurum duplicatum sp. nov. 4. forewing; 5. hind wing; 6. fore leg; 7. middle leg; 8. hind leg; 9. apex of hind leg; 10. male genitalia, lateral view; 11. anal tube, dorsal view; 12. penis, lateral view; 13. penis, dorsal view; 14. penis, ventral view; 15. capitulum of style, dorsal view; 16. female genitalia, ventral view; 17. anal tube, dorsal view; 18. gonocoxa VIII and gonapophyse VIII, lateral view; 19. gonapophyses IX, lateral view; 20. gonapophyses IX, dorsal view; 21. gonoplac, lateral view; 22. gonoplac, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216540/files/figure.png" pageId="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[1058,1074,260,284]" pageId="2" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,824]" pageId="2">Male genitalia. Symmetrical; anal tube mushroom-shaped. Posterior margin of pygofer not produced and without spines; penis tubular, U-shaped, symmetrical with two spiniform processes near mid-length.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,824]" pageId="2">Female genitalia. Anal tube cuplike, longer than widest part. Anterior connective lamina of gonapophyse VIII with teeth. Gonoplacs nearly triangular in lateral view.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,824]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,439,464]" pageId="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
In view of its elliptical body, the forewing without claval suture, its small hind wings (with vannus and anal lobe rudimentary and shorter than half of fore wings) and foliately dilated fore and middle femora, we treat this genus as a member of the tribe Parahiraciini. This genus resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Fennah" authorityName="Fennah" box="[1028,1244,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Neodurium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1028,1154,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="2">Neodurium</emphasis>
Fennah
</taxonomicName>
according to the lack of a claval suture in the forewing and the lateral margin of hind tibia bearing 
<number box="[1073,1087,548,572]" pageId="2" value="3.0">3</number>
teeth, but can be distinguished by the following characteristics: 
<number box="[521,533,584,608]" pageId="2" value="1.0">1</number>
) hind wing with vannus and anal lobe rudimentary (anal lobe only rudimentary in 
<taxonomicName box="[179,305,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Neodurium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[179,305,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="2">Neodurium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<number box="[329,344,620,644]" pageId="2" value="2.0">2</number>
) pronotum with median carina only present (median and lateral carinae present in 
<taxonomicName box="[1263,1389,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Neodurium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1263,1389,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="2">Neodurium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<number box="[1412,1426,620,644]" pageId="2" value="3.0">3</number>
) spinal formula of hind leg 
<number box="[449,461,656,680]" pageId="2" value="8.0">8</number>
– 
<number box="[477,489,656,680]" pageId="2" value="8.0">8</number>
– 
<number box="[505,519,656,680]" pageId="2" value="2.0">2</number>
(in 
<taxonomicName box="[564,690,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Neodurium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[564,690,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="2">Neodurium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<number box="[704,717,656,680]" pageId="2" value="8.0">8</number>
–(
<number box="[742,813,656,680]" pageId="2" value="15.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="11.0">11–19</number>
)– 
<number box="[837,852,656,680]" pageId="2" value="2.0">2</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,824]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,692,717]" pageId="2">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name “ 
<taxonomicName box="[471,624,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Folifemurum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Folifemurum</taxonomicName>
” is compiled from the Latin prefix “foli-” meaning leaf-shaped, and the Latin noun “femur”, together indicating the fore femur of this genus is slightly foliately dilated. This name is neutral in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,756,799,824]" pageId="2" type="distribution">
